item.description:
worksforme: <p>
On failure, fetch_feed() returns a WP_Error object instead of a Simplepie error. (You can see how this works by <a class="ext-link" href="http://core.trac.wordpress.org/browser/trunk/wp-includes/feed.php?rev=12883#L512"><span class="icon">​</span>looking at the code directly</a>.)
</p>
<p>
Thus, you'll need to do something like this:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">$feed = fetch_feed( $url );
if ( is_wp_error( $feed ) ) {
   echo $rss-&gt;get_error_message(); // a method of WP_Error
} else {
   // do your stuff here
}
</pre>
